00162 /*
00163  * IPF macro registers
00164  * ----------------------------------------------------------------------
00165  */
00166 
00167 enum
00168 {
00169   /* These need to be numbered starting after L_MAC_LAST in l_code.h
00170      since there is no way to distinguish better Lcode and machine specific
00171      macros. */
00172   TAHOE_MAC_ZERO = (L_MAC_LAST + 1),    /* R0                             */
00173   TAHOE_MAC_GP,                 /* data pointer  (R1)                     */
00174   TAHOE_MAC_AP,                 /* argument pointer  (R9)                 */
00175   TAHOE_MAC_RETADDR,            /* return address register                */
00176   TAHOE_MAC_PRED_TRUE,          /* P0                                     */
00177   TAHOE_MAC_FZERO,              /* Floating point register zero = 0.0     */
00178   TAHOE_MAC_FONE,               /* Floating point register one = 1.0      */
00179 
00180   TAHOE_PRED_SAVE_REG,
00181   TAHOE_PRED_BLK_REG,           /* pr                                     */
00182   TAHOE_PRED_ROT_BLK_REG,       /* pr.rot                                 */
00183 
00184   TAHOE_GP_SAVE_REG,
00185 
00186   TAHOE_MAC_TMPREG1,            /* r2 - Used for temp storage in phase2   */
00187   TAHOE_MAC_TMPREG2,            /* r3 - Used for temp storage in phase2   */
00188 
00189   TAHOE_MAC_LEAF,               /* 1 if leaf fn, 0 if not leaf function   */
00190   TAHOE_MAC_SYNC_SIZE,          /* size in bytes in LV space on stack     *
00191                                  * used to spill integers around syncs    *
00192                                  * such as setjmp                         */
00193   TAHOE_MAC_MEM_ALLOC,          /* total alloc space requirements         */
00194   TAHOE_MAC_TEMPLATE,
00195   TAHOE_MAC_LABEL,
00196 
00197   TAHOE_MAC_PSP,                /* Previous stack pointer (for alloca)    */
00198 
00199   TAHOE_MAC_PSPILL,             /* Predicate spill section pointer        */
00200 
00201 /* Application Registers - If these change, update application register
00202    macro check TAHOE_APPLICATION_MACRO( macro ).  These have been
00203    ordered by their application register number.*/
00204 
00205   /* M-type */
00206   TAHOE_MAC_KR0,                /* Kernel Register 0                      */
00207   TAHOE_MAC_KR1,                /* Kernel Register 1                      */
00208   TAHOE_MAC_KR2,                /* Kernel Register 2                      */
00209   TAHOE_MAC_KR3,                /* Kernel Register 3                      */
00210   TAHOE_MAC_RSC,                /* Register Stack Configuration Register  */
00211   TAHOE_MAC_BSP,                /* Backing Store Pointer for reg stack    */
00212   TAHOE_MAC_RNAT,               /* RSE NAT Collection register            */
00213   TAHOE_MAC_CCV,                /* Cmp/Exch Value Register                */
00214   TAHOE_MAC_UNAT,               /* User NAT Collection register           */
00215   TAHOE_MAC_FPSR,               /* Floating Point Status Register         */
00216   TAHOE_MAC_ITC,                /* Interval Time Counter                  */
00217   /* I-type */
00218   TAHOE_MAC_AR_PFS,             /* Previous Frame State                   */
00219   TAHOE_MAC_LC,                 /* Loop count                             */
00220   TAHOE_MAC_EC                  /* Epilogue stage counter                 */
00221 };

00223 #define TAHOE_APPLICATION_MACRO(macro)   ((TAHOE_I_APPLICATION_MACRO(macro)|| \
00224                                            TAHOE_M_APPLICATION_MACRO(macro)))
00225 
00226 #define TAHOE_M_APPLICATION_MACRO(macro) ((macro->value.mac >= TAHOE_MAC_KR0) \
00227                                           &&                                  \
00228                                           (macro->value.mac <= TAHOE_MAC_ITC))
00229 
00230 #define TAHOE_I_APPLICATION_MACRO(macro)                                      \
00231                                    ((macro->value.mac >= TAHOE_MAC_AR_PFS) && \
00232                                     (macro->value.mac <= TAHOE_MAC_EC))

00235 /*
00236  *    parameter and return value offsets
00237  */
00238 /*========================================================================*/
00239 /* 
00240  * 
00241  * Integers         P #'s
00242  * Using the register stack engine
00243  * 8 input parameters      0-7
00244  * 8 output parameters     8-15
00245  * 1 return (in static)    16 
00246  * 
00247  * Floats               P #'s
00248  * 
00249  * Don't use the register stack engine
00250  * 8 parameter registers   17-25
00251  * 1 return value          26
00252  * 
00253  */
00254
